# Zebrafish Social Preference Analysis

An interactive Google Colab notebook for analysing social preference behaviour
in zebrafish, using single-animal trajectory data exported from
[idtracker.ai](https://idtracker.ai/).

## What it does

Fish are recorded in a two-phase assay: first a **baseline** phase exploring an
empty arena, then a **test** phase after visual barriers are lifted to reveal
conspecifics on one side. The notebook quantifies whether a fish shifts toward
that social side once the stimulus appears, and compares this response across
experimental groups.

Given a folder of idtracker.ai sessions, the notebook will:

- **Scan & register** every session, reading trajectory metadata and locating
  each session's `background.png` and `ROI_mask.png`.
- **Derive zones automatically** from `ROI_mask.png`, splitting the arena into
  three vertical thirds (social / centre / far).
- **Normalise social side** by parsing the `_L`/`_R` suffix in each filename and
  horizontally flipping so the social third is always on the right ‚Äî making
  sessions poolable.
- **Quantify occupancy** in the social third for the before and after phases,
  reporting the difference and ratio, with per-phase tracking-quality checks.
- **Summarise per group** (mean ¬± SEM) and **export** everything to a
  multi-sheet Excel workbook for your own stats/plotting.
- **Visualise**: a QC contact sheet, per-fish before/after trajectory traces,
  a combined paired estimation plot with 95% confidence intervals, and pooled
  group-mean occupancy heatmaps on a shared colour scale.

## Input data

Arrange your sessions on Google Drive with one folder per experimental group:

```
my_data/                     <- point the notebook here
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ groupA/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 20250829_groupA_F1_L/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ preprocessing/   (background.png, ROI_mask.png)
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ trajectories/    (trajectories.npy)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ 20250829_groupA_F2_R/ ...
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ groupB/
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
```

Session folder names should follow `date_group_fish_side`, where `side` is
`L` or `R` (the side the conspecifics appear on). The top-level folder name
becomes the group label.

> **Tip:** you only need three files per session (`trajectories.npy`,
> `background.png`, `ROI_mask.png`). Uploading full idtracker.ai sessions
> including the `identification_images/*.h5` files is slow and unnecessary.

## How to run

1. Click the "Open in Colab" badge above.
2. Run the cells in order. Cell 1 installs dependencies; Cell 3 mounts your
   Drive and lets you point to your data folder.
3. Confirm the QC contact sheet looks right, set the before/after frame
   windows, and run through to the plots and Excel export.

## Requirements

Runs on Google Colab with no local setup. Key libraries: `traja`, `shapely`,
`numpy`, `pandas`, `matplotlib`, `scipy` (versions are pinned in Cell 1).

## Notes

This tool produces descriptive statistics and confidence intervals only ‚Äî it
does **not** run significance tests. Use the exported spreadsheet for your own
statistical analysis.
